<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I"><UNDER>AMENDED NOTICE OF MOTION</UNDER></TI>
<P>The Defendant, Lois Virgo, will make a motion to the a Judge on Tuesday, March 14, 2017;, at 10:00 a.m, or soon after that time as the motion can be heard, at 7765 Hurontario Street, Brampton, Ontario, L6W 4T6</P>
<P>PROPOSED METHOD OF HEARING:
<P1>The motion is to be heard orally.</P1></P>
<P>THE MOTION IS FOR
<P1>a) An Order abridging the time permitting the hearing of the motion on short notice to the Defendant, if necessary;</P1>
<P1>b) An Order abridging the time for filing the motion materials, if required;</P1>
<P1>c) An Order setting aside the Plaintiffs Default Judgment against the Defendant, Lois Virgo;</P1>
<P1>d) An Order directing the forthwith withdrawal of the Plaintiff's Writ of Execution and Garnishment against the Defendant Lois Virgo;</P1>
<P1>e) An Order directing the repayment of any funds received by the Plaintiff and or the Office of the Court Accountant to the Defendant herein on account of this action ;</P1>
<P1>f) Costs of this motion on a substantial indemnity basis; and</P1>
<P1>g) Such further and other relief as to this Honourable Court may seem just.</P1></P>
<P>THE GROUNDS FOR THE MOTION ARE
<P1>a) The Plaintiff commenced this action on or about May 15, 2009 and obtained default judgment against all the Defendants on or about September 2009;</P1>
<P1>b) The Plaintiff filed a Writ of Execution against all the Defendants on or about September 2009;</P1>
<P1>c) The Defendant Lois Virgo, the Moving Party herein (&ldquo;Ms. Virgo&rdquo;) is the former spouse of the Defendant Jeremy Renato Virgo (&ldquo;Mr. Virgo&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>d) On or about September 2008 and approximately nine (9) months before the Plaintiff commenced its action, the Virgos separated, Ms Virgo moved from the motrimonial home and she and her son moved into rental premises</P1>
<P1>e) Since separating from Mr. Virgo, Ms Virgo has had little, if any contact or communication with Mr. Virgo;</P1>
<P1>f) In 2012, Ms Virgo petitioned for divorce. Mr. Virgo failed to file a response, and to attend any of the divorce proceedings;</P1>
<P1>g) On July 4, 2014, Ms Virgo purchased a home for she and her son;</P1>
<P1>h) The existence of the Plaintiff's Writ of Execution, its Judgment, and this action first became known to Ms Virgo during the last week of May 2014 as a result of various searches conducted in respect of her pending house purchase;</P1>
<P1>i) Ms Virgo was neither an officer, director, shareholder nor a participant (active or otherwise) in any of the Defendant companies/enterprises, nor in the financial affairs of Mr. Virgo, before or during their marriage.</P1>
<P1>j) She does recall signing a series of Bank of Nova Scotia loan documents sent to her by Mr. Virgo in 2005 while she was on a business trip to Jamaica, but the particulars of the documents and the event itself are vague given that more than a decade has passed.</P1>
<P1>k) In June 2014, the counsel herein failed to reach an agreement as to the setting aside of the Default Judgment against and the Writ of Execution filed against Ms. Virgo, counsel for Ms Virgo served its Notice of Motion (on a urgent basis) and Motion Record upon counsel for the Plaintiff and arranged for the filing of the motion materials.
<P2>(Counsel for Ms Virgo intends, to rely upon the documentary evidence contained in the Motion Record served upon the Plantiff's Counsel in June of 2014)</P2></P1>
<P1>l) After confirming receipt of the said motion materials, counsel for the Plaintiff consented to the withdrawal of the Writ of Execution against Ms Virgo in order to permit her pending house purchase to close;</P1>
<P1>m) The matter of the Default Judgment against Ms Virgo, the sufficiency of service upon her and her liability to the Plaintiff, if any at all, were deferred for further negation;</P1>
<P1>n) Subsequent discussions between counsel failed to resolve the outstanding issues and on or about November 8, 2016, the Plaintiff served a Notice of Garnishment upon Ms Virgo's employer;</P1>
<P1>o) On December 13, 2016, the Plaintiff's counsel was served with a Notice of Return of Motion which erroneously indicated that the motion would be heard on Friday, December 24, 2016. December 24, 2016 was in fact a Saturday;</P1>
<P1>p) After further fruitless settlement discussions, on December 23, 2016, counsel for the Plaintiff was again served with an amended Notice of Return of Motion to set aside and stay enforcement of the Plaintiff's Default Judgment. The amended Notice of Motion indicated that the returnable date was January 12, 2017;</P1>
<P1>q) On or about January 10, 2017, counsel for Ms Virgo became aware of the fact that the initial (June 2014) Motion materials to set aside and stay enforcement of the Plaintiff's Default Judgment, had not filed with the Court on account of the fact that word that the Plaintiff's counsel had consented to adjourn the subject motion and withdraw the Writ of Execution against Ms Virgo was conveyed to the process server before he had actually filed the motion materials but after he had collected them for filing;</P1>
<P1>m) Serious issues exists as to:
<P2>i. whether or not Ms Virgo had knowledge of the Plaintiff's claim prior to May, 2014;</P2>
<P2>ii. whether or not Ms Virgo was properly served with notice of the Plaintiff's action;</P2>
<P2>iii. the capacity under which Ms Virgo was named a Defendant, be it as co-applicant, an officer and/or director, a personal guarantor, or a consenting spouse, as well as to what extent, if at all, she is liable to the Plaintiff; and additionally</P2>
<P2>iv. whether or not she was entitled to independent legal advice prior to agreeing to act as a guarantor of the corporate and personal loans made by the Plaintiff to Mr. Virgo and his companies, and if so,</P2>
<P2>v) whether or not she received independent legal advice;</P2></P1>
<P1>n) The Defendant, Lois Virgo will rely on Rules 1.04 (1), 2.01(a), 2.03, 3.02(1), and (2), 16.07 and 19.08 of the Rules <UNDER>of Civil Procedure</UNDER>; and</P1>
<P1>o) Such further and other grounds as counsel for the Moving Party Defendant may advise.</P1></P>
<P>THE FOLLOWING DOCUMENTARY EVIDENCE will be used at the hearing of the motion:
<P1>a) The Affidavit of Lois Virgo, sworn June 28, 2014</P1>
<P1>b) The Affidavit of Fatima Melo, sworn June 30, 2014</P1>
<P1>c) Such further and other evidence counsel may advise and this Honourable Court may permit.</P1></P>
