<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II"><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT of FATIMA MELO</UNDER></TI>
<P>I, Fatima Melo, of the City of Mississauga, in the Regional Municipality of Peel, in the Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY:</P>
<P>1. I am a law clerk in the employ of Bodkin Law, counsel for the Defendant, Lois Virgo, and as such, I have knowledge of the matters contained herein this my Affidavit.</P>
<P>2. In the course of my duties as Mr. Bodkin's senior real estate law clerk, I conducted a series of searches in respect of Ms Virgo's pending real property purchase which is scheduled to close on July 4, 2014.</P>
<P>3. My search for writs of executions against Ms Virgo's name revealed the Plaintiff's Writ of Execution, File Number 09-5436, filed with the Brampton Sheriff on September 10, 2009. Attached hereto this my Affidavit and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the said Writ Details Report.</P>
<P>4. At the direction of Mr. Bodkin, I forwarded an email to counsel for the Judgment Creditor in this matter, requesting:
<P1>(i) copies of documents pertaining the Plaintiff's action given that Ms Virgo had no knowledge of the action and, at best, a vague recollection of certain events possibly related to the underlying transaction; and</P1>
<P1>(ii) opposing counsel's co-operation in facilitating the completion of Ms Virgo's pending real estate transaction, and in possibly resolving the Plaintiff's action in an efficient and just manner.</P1></P>
<P>5. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> of this my Affidavit is a copy of Mr. Bodkin's email to opposing counsel which I forwarded on June 25, 2014.</P>
<P>6. Later the same day, I received opposing counsel's response in our firm's general email box denying Mr. Bodkin's request for documents and assistance in resolving the matter cooperatively.</P>
<P>7. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> of this my Affidavit is a copy of opposing counsel's response thereby necessitating the hearing of this matter on an urgent basis.</P>
<P>8. I make the Affidavit in support of a motion to set aside the Plaintiff's Default Judgment as against Lois Virgo; to stay enforcement of the said Judgment as against Lois Virgo, to withdraw the Writ of Execution filed against Lois Virgo, and for the costs of the motion and for no other or improper purpose.</P>
