<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I"><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT of LOIS VIRGO</UNDER></TI>
<P>I, Lois Virgo, of the City of Mississauga, in the Regional Municipality of Peel, in the Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY:</P>
<P>1. I am the former spouse of Jeremy Renato Neil Virgo, also known as Jeremy Virgo (hereafter &ldquo;Mr. Virgo&rdquo;), a Co-Defendant in this action. We were married on January 1, 2000 in Kingston, Jamaica.</P>
<P>2. Mr. Virgo was the owner, operator and directing mind of the other Co-Defendants in this action, Renatoneil Consultants Ltd. and Wave Zone.</P>
<P>3. I was never included in, had any knowledge of, or was ever involved in any of Mr. Virgo's various business ventures and affairs. In fact, I now know that I was purposefully excluded from his business affairs. Furthermore, during our marriage we maintained largely separate lives and finances.</P>
<P>4. I have never been an officer, director or shareholder in Renatoneil Consultants Ltd. (hereafter &ldquo;Renatoneil&rdquo;), nor have I ever had any role whatsoever in the management or the affairs of Renatoneil.</P>
<P>5. I have never been an owner, partner nor investor in Wave Zone, nor have I ever had any role whatsoever in the management or the affairs of Wave Zone.</P>
<P>6. Notwithstanding my non-involvement of in either Renatoneil and Wave Zone, I recall that while visiting my parents in Jamaica, in late January 2005, I received an urgent call from Mr. Virgo advising me that he had arranged bank financing for one of his businesses, everything had been approved but the Bank of Nova Scotia required my signature on a couple of documents since I was his spouse.</P>
<P>7. Either the next day or the day after, Mr. Virgo sent certain documents pertaining to a Bank of Nova Scotia business loan which is the subject of this action to me in Jamaica and arranged for me to attend at a lawyer to have them witnessed.</P>
<P>8. I was advised by Mr. Virgo, and verily do believe, that my signature was all that was need for the loan to be processed, that he required the funds in order to take care of some long standing and urgent matters, and that upon the Bank receiving the said signed documents, funds would be released to him.</P>
<P>9. Whether or not this was actually the case I do not know, I only know what I was advised Mr. Virgo in our long distance telephone conversation.</P>
<P>10. At his request, I attended a lawyer's office in Kingston, Jamaica. The lawyer with whom I met was named Yolande Whitely.</P>
<P>11. Ms Whitely, briefly reviewed the document which Mr. Virgo sent to me with me, witnessed my signature on the said document and in approximately fifteen to twenty minutes after arriving at her office, I departed her office and couriered the signed documents back to Mr. Virgo in Toronto.</P>
<P>12. As I had no involvement in the affairs of Renatoneil nor Wave Zone, I was not privy as to how the loan was obtained, its terms, nor the manner in which the loan was serviced by Mr. Virgo, Renatoneil and/or Wave Zone.</P>
<P>13. Additionally, I certainly did not receive any portion of the advance from the said business loan from the Plaintiff, Mr. Virgo, Renatoneil nor Wave Zone.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI>Separation and Divorce</TI>
<P>14. In September, 2008, Mr. Virgo and I had become irreconcilably estranged, when I learned that he had conceived a child with his business partner and that the child was then two years old. I moved from the matrimonial home and since that time, Mr. Virgo and I have had little, if any, contact.</P>
<P>15. I filed for divorce in December 2011, and at that time I had no idea nor the slightest notion that I was saddled with Mr. Virgo's Bank of Nova Scotia business loan (the &ldquo;Loan&rdquo;), moreover that the Plaintiff in these proceedings had obtained default judgment against me in 2009.</P>
<P>16. Consequently, when I filed for divorce, neither the Plaintiff's loan nor its Default Judgment were addressed in my Net Family Property Statement, my Petition for Divorce, or in my Divorce Order, notwithstanding my profound hurt and disappointment and my desire to ensure that I did all that I possibly could do to make a fresh start for myself and our son.</P>
<P>17. My petition for Divorce was granted on May 15, 2012. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the my Divorce Order.</P>
<P>18. On May 18, 2014, I entered into an Agreement of Purchase and Sale for a townhome for my son and me. This transaction is scheduled to close on July 4, 2014.</P>
<P>19. On or about May 23, 2014, I received a telephone message Mr. Bodkin's real estate clerk, that an execution search revealed an Execution in favour of the Plaintiff against me.</P>
<P>20. Believing that the subject execution was a mistake given the zeal with which I manage my credit, or that it pertained to a Bank of Nova Scotia car loan which I paid in full in January 2013, I contacted my branch of the Bank of Nova Scotia which confirmed that my car loan had in fact been paid off and that they had no idea what gave rise to the execution.</P>
<P>21. Further investigation revealed that the Plainitiff's execution against me pertained to the Plaintiff's 2004 business loan to Mr. Virgo guaranteed by me in Jamaica in February 2005 an urgent basis for Mr. Virgo.</P>
<P>22. I am advised and verily do believe that as early as June 25, 2014, shortly after I first became aware the Plaintiff's action, its default judgment and execution against me, the Plaintiff was made aware of the following facts:
<P1><EM>a)</EM> my non-involvement in and lack of knowledge with respect to the affairs of Renatoneil, Wave Zone and Mr. Virgo's related business affairs, and</P1>
<P1><EM>b)</EM> the apparent irregularities and uncertainties with respect to the independent legal advice rendered to me on behalf of the Plaintiff and upon which it continues to rely.</P1>
<P1>Attached hereto as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; is an email addressed to the counsel for the Plaintiff advising the Plaintiff accordingly.</P1></P>
<P>23. I make the Affidavit in support of the dismissal of the Motion for summary judgement against me and for no other or improper purpose.</P>
